# UNIVERSAL .gitignore
#
# Purpose:
#   This file is designed as a universal .gitignore for both monorepos and
#   single-repos, providing support for multi-language, multi-toolchain,
#   and multi-OS environments.
#
# Supported Languages (non-exhaustive):
#   - JavaScript / TypeScript / Node.js
#   - Python
#   - Rust
#   - Go
#   - Zig
#   - C / C++
#   - C# / .NET
#   - Kotlin / JVM
#
# Supported Environments:
#   - Linux (including Arch-based)
#   - macOS
#   - Windows
#
# Design Principles:
#   - Ignore build artifacts, caches, temporary files, and local tooling state.
#   - Keep source code, configs, and reproducible definitions tracked.
#   - Safe for monorepos, CI/CD, and cross-editor workflows.
#
# Notes:
#   - Certain lock files (e.g., Cargo.lock, go.sum, etc.) may be adjusted
#     depending on the project type (library vs. application).
#   - This file is opinionated yet conservative (avoiding over-ignoring).
#
# Created and curated by Nazator
# https://nazator.com
# https://github.com/nazator/hyperedge

